Last night was a long-awaited night. With all of the changes and things that were taken away from these kids, we are so happy they got to have prom! Special thanks to Tianna O'Neill and Diana Williams for the decor, KTown Sound (Joey) for DJing, Finney's for catering, and Bill and Sarah Scoville for dessert! The night wouldn't have been possible without all of you!
Without further ado, I present "A Night in Paradise"!

**As always, the pictures that are or are not here are not on purpose or with any personal bias. This is what turned out, at least partially! (I apologize in advance that I did not get a good group picture of the seniors! DeeAnn would have some for purchase!) Feel free to share, tag, print, etcetera!**

Edit- Apparently Facebook's latest update has taken away my ability to tag anyone who is not my 'friend' even if he/she is a member of the Parent Page. I apologize! Please tag yourself and your friends as you are able!

Erika Kappel‎Parents of the S-E-M kids
May 31 at 6:35 PM ·

Hello all! Tomorrow is June 1st and we will begin a "modified" running club for cross country. We will be having a mileage challenge this summer for the months of June and July. The miles/workouts put in will be on the athletes own for convenience purposes. Just text/message me how many miles you run per workout and I will keep a running total. The CC runner with the most miles put in this summer will receive a prize at the beginning of conditioning week this fall.

If students were not out for CC last year and are planning on being out this fall, please get a hold of Coach Kappel so she can keep them posted on summer announcements! Thanks all!
text:
Erika Kappel‎Parents of the S-E-M kids
May 31 at 6:35 PM ·

Hello all! Tomorrow is June 1st and we will begin a "modified" running club for cross country. We will be having a mileage challenge this summer for the months of June and July. I have an additional update regarding summer driver’s education. The Safety Center has decided to not hold range for schools outside of Kearney this summer due to COVID-19. Thank you for your understanding and we hope to be able to have your students back at the range for next summer’s classes!



DeAnn Keith, Traffic Specialist

Good morning SEM families, this is Mr. Schmidt.

I hope all of the Mothers had a great Mother's Day yesterday.

Mr. Doud and I have been doing 3 zoom sessions a day to help students register. Current Freshmen are today, and current 8th graders are tomorrow. Please contact me if you have any quesitons.

I have set a goal for students to have their work completed by this Friday, as that will allow teachers to grade things and return them, and allow corrections to be made by the 20th. The final day of school is May 20th and assignments not completed by that day will be deemed incomplete. We will have students complete those assignments through the ICU process in the fall, to help them in their educational process.

Thank you to everyone that worked so hard during this new process. I think we all learned a lot, and are better prepared for the future.

The school board meeting is tonight at 8:00 pm, and the zoom link is on the school website and on the Facebook page.

Have a great week and GO MUSTANGS.

post_text:
The Nebraska Promise: Attend Nebraska, Tuition-Free at UNK, UNO or UNL

The Nebraska Promise program covers undergraduate tuition at the University of Nebraska (UNO, UNK and UNL) for students who have a family income of $60,000 or less (Adjusted Gross Income/AGI) or are Pell Grant-eligible, and who meet academic requirements.

Nearly 3,000 students currently attend NU tuition-free under Collegebound Nebraska. The expanded Nebraska Promise will cover approximately 1,000 additional current and future NU students. Through this program, our desire is to expand access and support Nebraskans who may not have thought they could afford a university education.

You can learn more about the Nebraska Promise, eligibility and renewal criteria and find an FAQ at the link below:

LEARN MORE ABOUT THE NEBRASKA PROMISE »

Good morning elementary students! We have a READING challenge for you and your class for the month of April. I will continue to total AR reading points for the month of April and the class that has the highest average points will earn a pizza party and games when we get back to school. There will even be a "unique" trophy for the winning class. Might be something else that I am working on, but no promises. Some of you have already gotten a jump on other classes with your reading totals already! Remember to take time for yourself while you are at home and this is a great chance to do so with reading.

Miss you all so very much! It was soooooo good to see many of you and your parents the other night at the parade! Happy Easter!!

Please don't hesitate to call me if you have questions, just not over Easter weekend🤣 That was a joke for those of you that don't know me. Happy early Easter!

Senior Parents: I am sure some of you have questions about the remainder of the school year with scholarships. I have called all seniors to see how they are doing and to answer any questions they might have. Before we left on Monday, I encouraged seniors to continue to work on scholarships and to email me any completed scholarships that needed to be returned to me. When I receive their scholarship, I will email them back to confirm I received the scholarship. I have called several senior parents this week and will try to get in contact with each senior parent over the next week. If you have questions, please don't hesitate to contact me by phone (308)390-7248 or email rdoud@semmustangs.org

I will continue to log daily on my counseling web page. If you have not been on it, here is the link. http://doudscounselingcorner.weebly.com

I am so impressed with the students as they learn to work remotely and to plan and develop their daily schedules. There are several local scholarship due April 1. Check in with them to see how they are doing. Thank you!! Mr. Doud

During a school closing, Happy Numbers is here to work with teachers to ensure the uninterrupted education of PK-5 students. We help teachers deliver quality math instruction and monitor progress and math growth - all remotely.

To ease the challenge of transitioning to online instruction, Happy Numbers is offering free access for the rest of the school year - no strings attached:

>>> Go to HappyNumbers.com to sign up.

Students can access Happy Numbers from any Internet-enabled device (even a smartphone!). They can start learning remotely today to ensure they don’t fall behind -- in just 15 mins a day, 4 times a week.

March 17 at 10:18 AM ·

During a school closing, Happy Numbers is here to work with teachers to ensure the uninterrupted education of PK-5 students. We help teachers deliver quality math instruction and monitor progress and math growth - all remotely.

To ease the challenge of transitioning to online instruction, Happy Numbers is offering free access for the rest of the school year - no strings attached:

>>> Go to HappyNumbers.com to sign up.

Students can access Happy Numbers from any Internet-enabled device (even a smartphone!). They can start learning remotely today to ensure they don’t fall behind -- in just 15 mins a day, 4 times a week.

Due to the current school closing and the recommendations from public health officials to avoid holding events with groups of people greater than 10 the SEM School Foundation has POSTPONED the Talent Show that was scheduled for March 27th and 28th. We will see how things go the next couple of weeks and how other activities are rescheduled before making a decision on when to have the Talent Show. We will announce updates as we assess the situation.
The foundation board would like to thank the community for your continued support.
